"children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"133","text":"Electrolitos (K, Mg, Ca)","guid":"YsK9r_9hTRyCPPYy6FelrA","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"133","text":"Funcion hepatica","guid":"mCkYZHtWQMSLqvc-NprWUg","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"133","text":"Funcion renal","guid":"vhG8rXvUR7afGvDk2jI3XA","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"133","text":"Hemograma","guid":"7qfQTDqqTBiYDmGSB64vCw","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"133","text":"Prolactina y CK","guid":"xbHgX-Y4RZ2Dkk07Wh5_5Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"140","parent":"132","text":"Durante tratamiento","guid":"zO_63g_KTzGIaDqocOP73A","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"QTc → con cada cambio de dosis","guid":"o3_zhXyhR66IJ7BdBVgtdg","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"140","text":"Signos extrapiramidales → evaluacion clinica diaria","guid":"tUbPbrQHS8CoIjB_E8Y_pA","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"140","text":"Nivel de sedacion","guid":"-Z7C957YRCKeL4VPnyYVJA","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"140","text":"Presion arterial ortostatica","guid":"c8t1IgyeQJ-C7ULKk5jaGg","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"140","text":"Peso, IMC → mensual si uso prolongado","guid":"P2Bg6P2TTaOe2_BEm7UILA","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"140","text":"Perfil lipidico, glucosa → mes 3 y anual","guid":"CxnEi7VVTLO5KG-BiAOdDA","children":[]}]},{"id":"147","parent":"132","text":"Criterios de suspension","guid":"Z7parrJhRsagwyc7CJAphg","children":[{"id":"148","parent":"147","text":"Resolucion del delirium → suspender en 1-7 dias","guid":"MmHoqh5wQImhg4ocfRbhtQ","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"147","text":"QTc >500 ms","guid":"JY-SmVp_RT2D1skePqYS5g","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"147","text":"Fiebre + rigidez → sospecha SNM","guid":"jWM6UszTQe-mw6BBxeUaXA","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"147","text":"SEP severos no manejables con reduccion de dosis","guid":"RGTEtN-KTvqTtrTKJbI0Ig","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"147","text":"Demencia → reevaluar a 1-3 meses de control sintomas","guid":"xAoyFejAS7Wq9L8771L8ew","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"0","text":"Comparacion con Alternativas","guid":"PSVgS-WSRCaX-fobMSe_XA","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"vs Quetiapina","guid":"9fohfq_CTNGnFosfPY_Z1w","children":[{"id":"155","parent":"154","text":"Quetiapina → disociacion rapida D2, menos SEP","guid":"UCWaVS2BTs2JbhI7US90nw","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"154","text":"Quetiapina → PREFERIDA en Parkinson/DCL","guid":"XDyIOJ_2QvqIZTWW94SGjA","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"154","text":"Quetiapina → mas sedante (H1) a dosis bajas","guid":"VD1NXrdsQTmkylNuP3pV6g","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"154","text":"Quetiapina → efecto antipsicótico real requiere >200 mg","guid":"NYXQnphnQNCE62D2VqFrQA","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"154","text":"Haloperidol → mas potente, via parenteral disponible","guid":"XjQsSXO1Qw6WC543APucyg","children":[]}]},{"id":"160","parent":"153","text":"vs Risperidona","guid":"dp1AzvMhQ8CvQ7XLtRH88A","children":[{"id":"161","parent":"160","text":"Risperidona → unico aprobado en agresividad Alzheimer","guid":"n2OvhkT2ROqf_V9peq5aZw","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"160","text":"Risperidona → menos SEP a dosis bajas (<2 mg)","guid":"8iavlLjnS6ec4XQ2ffzGnA","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"160","text":"Risperidona → riesgo ACV en demencia","guid":"Py3goDOOTK6BwSUA8mc9YQ","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"160","text":"Haloperidol → preferido si no hay via oral","guid":"1r_sJpEPTiSk7fAxbjXQUQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"165","parent":"153","text":"vs Olanzapina","guid":"nW-Rr4jyRZyUE5k5n-mRjw","children":[{"id":"166","parent":"165","text":"Olanzapina → muy sedante, orexigena","guid":"nVdST4A1T4qt59kmtUkzhQ","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"165","text":"Olanzapina → efecto anticolinergico (M1) → EMPEORA delirium","guid":"JlqXkx_5TaSsiLqjwKM-qA","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"165","text":"Olanzapina → mejor en DFT","guid":"wAfkQGrdRYGQrYS0MzNHZw","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"165","text":"Haloperidol → sin carga anticolinergica","guid":"kwZIF_1mTcOIx4eHHqtzRw","children":[]}]},{"id":"170","parent":"153","text":"vs Dexmedetomidina (UCI)","guid":"ENHENQ3SSBa6T87DhFvOzw","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"Dexmedetomidina → primera linea sedacion AM critico (PADIS 2025)","guid":"PZsAX2YzTXmPbqnVpOXEHw","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"170","text":"Dexmedetomidina → menos delirium que BZD","guid":"YvtQBLnMTgmk45SlP2wAaA","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"170","text":"Haloperidol → complemento, no primera linea en UCI actual","guid":"mdtyTN0HQv-UwvpeHle9rA","children":[]}]},{"id":"174","parent":"153","text":"vs Tiapride","guid":"r2i7OHN9S9O9zZK9vKX2qw","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"Tiapride → eficacia similar, menos SEP","guid":"Hv8XmzkIQn6fxJVxu9FQ7w","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"174","text":"Tiapride → indicacion en agitacion del anciano","guid":"jtErt9qcSxek4ZOYgSMTeQ","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"174","text":"Tiapride → alternativa parenteral (100-200 mg IM)","guid":"bqg7U9t4RSepTSfEoK16Dw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"178","parent":"0","text":"Evidencia Clave","guid":"fxnh6mcRQwG2ppR9byoQkg","children":[{"id":"179","parent":"178","text":"Profilaxis POD","guid":"tieoMX6ATmCSgItY9g4x2w","children":[{"id":"180","parent":"179","text":"NMA 2025 (Liu et al, J Psychiatr Res) → OR 0.42 (IC 0.25-0.71) vs placebo","guid":"d_xg78DmT8m04FR_zT8IGA","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"179","text":"Atipicos mas efectivos que haloperidol en prevencion (OR 0.27)","guid":"rGlG4cTmRcSsxgCT5-V4Hw","children":[]}]},{"id":"182","parent":"178","text":"Tratamiento delirium","guid":"UtUF3ZuQRw6R8eE3g8S89g","children":[{"id":"183","parent":"182","text":"Eficacia similar a atipicos en reducir severidad","guid":"HnBWPDppTwKVX3t-kA9v0w","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"182","text":"Inferior a placebo en algunos estudios paliativos","guid":"YgLBgz_ZQX2nuJehiZwkog","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"182","text":"Dosis promedio real en AM ≥65a → 2.75 mg/dia (mayor a lo recomendado)","guid":"rZiyReBhQ6-Nsw07SW62qw","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"182","text":"Dosis promedio en UCI → 8.45 mg/dia","guid":"dt122DL4Slyibf4MY2N6xg","children":[]}]},{"id":"187","parent":"178","text":"Mortalidad en demencia","guid":"bBPATJz2TF2k8cpVd1doRw","children":[{"id":"188","parent":"187","text":"HR mortalidad 1.5x vs APSG","guid":"pKW_McllQaiL4tH9GDlmJg","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"187","text":"Black Box Warning FDA 2005 (atipicos) y 2008 (tipicos)","guid":"zbqtckkPQJekFvLj2OXk0A","children":[]}]},{"id":"190","parent":"178","text":"Caidas y fracturas","guid":"8CvmWzt1QPKEtXV9tk0plQ","children":[{"id":"191","parent":"190","text":"HR fracturas 1.39","guid":"f53EU6mAT_esQe2FyHuMGg","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"190","text":"HR fractura cadera 1.76","guid":"vB7TMgOHRiueC7q_vBVgoA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"193","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clinicas","guid":"QD3ZWWJjQVet98yYEZz7iw","children":[{"id":"194","parent":"193","text":"Dosis baja (≤0.5 mg) en AM naive → similar eficacia a dosis mayores, menos RAM","guid":"5FagwQCmSkKowH-Cp8HmoQ","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"193","text":"NUNCA escalar dosis si aparece inquietud motora → pensar AKATISIA primero","guid":"UgGfKk8MQr2hL0E2oaiX7A","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"193","text":"Sin efecto anticolinergico → ventaja clave sobre olanzapina/clorpromazina en delirium","guid":"AbsPwRiVSUOB4NKS9Ff0QQ","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"193","text":"QTc y electrolitos → K >4.0, Mg >2.0 OBLIGATORIOS antes de carga IV en UCI","guid":"1YePnNFyTEO-WW6TGLMJpA","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"193","text":"En demencia → haloperidol SOLO urgencias sin via oral, NUNCA rutinario","guid":"aH_0_H4eTXWntGyyB9haYg","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"193","text":"DCL/Parkinson → CONTRAINDICADO, usar quetiapina o clozapina","guid":"8c8l0tFeSWWfzBrZdbqtvg","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"193","text":"Delirium por deprivacion OH/BZD → NO usar haloperidol, benzodiacepinas son primera linea","guid":"UHfGweQIR1yrccX8PXDDmQ","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"193","text":"Quetiapina 25-100 mg → efecto hipnotico (H1), NO antipsicótico real (requiere >200 mg D2)","guid":"9PP-9UjaR8ysHL9NcHo3ug","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"193","text":"El no tratar tambien es riesgo → inhibicion terapeutica genera deterioro funcional y sufrimiento","guid":"ow70VaxzSAiUuX8JlgfIOA","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"193","text":"Siempre documentar en HC → balance beneficio/riesgo, consentimiento, uso off-label","guid":"k5pLgONGQACWJDh0XiD9lA","children":[]}]},{"id":"204","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"FiaQEkJGSsiDN2GQSGkDJQ","children":[{"id":"205","parent":"204","text":"1. Devlin JW et al. CPG for Pain, Agitation, Delirium, Immobility, Sleep (PADIS). Crit Care Med. 2018;46(9):e825-e873.","guid":"zQXrR3P2RbKcTvVijnEhVw","children":[]},{"id":"206","parent":"204","text":"2. Lewis K et al. Focused Update PADIS. Crit Care Med. 2025;53(3):e711-e727.","guid":"H4dY7udgRTaTB4kq694XNQ","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"204","text":"3. Inouye SK. Delirium in older persons. N Engl J Med. 2006;354(11):1157-65.","guid":"HovjR3QiSj6lpLu4X0eKLQ","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"204","text":"4. Liu TH et al. Pharmacologic prophylaxis of POD in elderly: NMA. J Psychiatr Res. 2025;181:169-178.","guid":"Tvdbx8QETG2GIlsOspzQ5Q","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"204","text":"5. Neufeld KJ et al. Antipsychotic for delirium: systematic review. J Am Geriatr Soc. 2016;64(4):705-14.","guid":"3aWtq64ARg2njFfdZ6VdLA","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"204","text":"6. Wang P et al. Risk of death: conventional vs atypical antipsychotics. N Engl J Med. 2005;353:2335-41.","guid":"acm7bVSNS3OwmL-wCUnZ3Q","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"204","text":"7. NICE. Delirium: prevention, diagnosis, management. CG103. Updated 2019.","guid":"hUnSaNKMQ12aXC9lYPb7QQ","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"204","text":"8. Shen YZ et al. Effects of haloperidol on delirium: SR and MA. Med Princ Pract. 2018;27:250-259.","guid":"eAoXaxMCR02VNb6sx9ghMA","children":[]},{"id":"213","parent":"204","text":"9. Guia de uso de antipsicóticos en personas mayores (documento interno Drive).","guid":"xwXxN5ubRFW7FGWcGlaU3Q","children":[{"id":"214","parent":"213","text":"11. MSF Medical Guidelines. Haloperidol oral. 2024.","guid":"c9ePt6jsRDuY0hX6R4bQvQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"215","parent":"204","text":"10. Guia mecanismo de accion antipsicóticos (documento interno Drive).","guid":"YHNo8rWwSUeKnYNZ9EoSoQ","children":[]},{"id":"216","parent":"204","text":"12. MHRA. Review of haloperidol in elderly patients with acute delirium. Public Assessment Report. 2021.","guid":"90sUZbKaRmaozS_wfczcCA","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":216,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Farmacología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Farmacología","filename":"Haloperidol","id":"map_598","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Haloperidol"}